The following are major news items in leading Philippine
newspapers today: Manila Bulletin, Philippine Star: -- A helicopter on
a test flight plunged into a basketball court in a subdivision in
Cavite yesterday, killing a senior air transport official and a flight
mechanic. Philippine Journal, Star: -- Businessmen interested in
participating in the development of Club John Hay in Baguio city are
required to make a minimum investment of 100 million US dollars within
three years, the bases conversion development authority said yesterday.
Philippine Daily Inquirer, Chronicle: -- The military and the MORO
Islamic Liberation Front have agreed to expand their localized peace
talks to western Mindanao, particularly the troubled provinces of
Basilan and Sulu.
